                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00111 Armament Control/67c: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-06T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 6, 1935—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>161. Suggest you take any precautionary measures you may consider appropriate for
                    the protection of American citizens in case of reaction by Italians against
                    President’s Proclamation of Arms Embargo and travel on belligerent ships.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
